    <abstract>Du Jiwen sees strong ties between the inscriptions and the activities of "An Daoyi" and early Chan Buddhism. Shandong chan is said to have belonged to the Northern school. He quotes the Jingde zhuandeng lu in identifying two disciples of Shenxiu as 
    chan masters from Shandong (山東崇遠法師 and 東丘降魔, who was also known as 兖州降魔世藏. He thinks that Chan Buddhism, while withdrawing from Luoyang and Ye and wandering southwards to Shanxi and Anhui, must have passed Shandong.</abstract>
